{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "FHIR Validator — GITB REST Processing Services",
    "description": "GITB-compatible REST processing service endpoints for the HL7 FHIR Validator.\nEach service exposes GET /definition (metadata) and POST /process (execute).\nAll input/output values are strings. JSON objects (FHIR resources) are passed as stringified JSON.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "contact": {
      "name": "HL7 FHIR Core Team",
      "url": "https://github.com/hapifhir/org.hl7.fhir.core"
    }
  },
  "servers": [
    { "url": "http://localhost:8080/itb", "description": "Local development server" }
  ],
  "paths": {
    "/fhirpath/definition": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["FHIRPath"],
        "summary": "FHIRPathProcessor — service definition",
        "operationId": "fhirpathDefinition",
        "description": "Returns GITB service metadata.\n\nService id: `FHIRPathProcessor`\nOperations: `evaluate`, `assert`\n\n`assert` is a special case of `evaluate` where the expression is expected to evaluate to a boolean. The operation reports `SUCCESS` only when the result is `true`; a `false` result yields `FAILURE`. Any non-boolean result also yields `FAILURE`.\n\n**Inputs:**\n| Name | Type | Required |\n|------|------|----------|\n| content | string (FHIR JSON) | yes |\n| expression | string (FHIRPath) | yes |\n\n**Outputs:**\n| Name | Type |\n|------|------|\n| result | string (evaluate: stringified value; assert: `true`/`false`) |",
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Service definition", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ServiceDefinition" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/fhirpath/process": {
      "post": {
        "tags": ["FHIRPath"],
        "summary": "Evaluate or assert a FHIRPath expression",
        "operationId": "fhirpathProcess",
        "description": "**evaluate:** Evaluates `inputs.expression` against `inputs.content` (stringified FHIR JSON). Returns the first result as a string. Booleans return `true`/`false`.\n\n**assert:** Same evaluation, but the expression must yield a boolean. `result: SUCCESS` only when the value is `true`; `false` (or a non-boolean result) yields `result: FAILURE`.",
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["operation", "inputs"],
                "properties": {
                  "operation": { "type": "string", "enum": ["evaluate", "assert"] },
                  "inputs": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": ["content", "expression"],
                    "properties": {
                      "content": { "type": "string", "description": "FHIR resource (or other FHIRPath context) as stringified JSON" },
                      "expression": { "type": "string", "description": "FHIRPath expression" }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "examples": {
                "evaluate": {
                  "summary": "Read a value out of a resource",
                  "value": { "operation": "evaluate", "inputs": { "content": "{\"resourceType\":\"Patient\",\"name\":[{\"family\":\"Smith\"}]}", "expression": "Patient.name.family" } }
                },
                "assert": {
                  "summary": "Check a boolean expression",
                  "value": { "operation": "assert", "inputs": { "content": "{\"resourceType\":\"Patient\",\"name\":[{\"family\":\"Smith\"}]}", "expression": "Patient.name.family = 'Smith'" } }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Result",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ProcessResponse" },
                "examples": {
                  "evaluate": { "summary": "evaluate result", "value": { "result": "SUCCESS", "output": { "result": "Smith" } } },
                  "assert": { "summary": "assert succeeded", "value": { "result": "SUCCESS", "output": { "result": "true" } } }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/fhir/definition": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Validator"],
        "summary": "FHIRValidator — service definition",
        "operationId": "fhirDefinition",
        "description": "Returns GITB service metadata.\n\nService id: `FHIRValidator`\nOperations: `validate`, `loadIG`\n\n**Inputs:**\n| Name | Type | Required | Used by |\n|------|------|----------|---------|\n| content | string (FHIR JSON/XML/Turtle) | yes (validate) | validate |\n| contentType | string (MIME type) | no (default `application/fhir+json`) | validate |\n| profiles | string (comma-separated URLs) | no | validate |\n| ig | string (package#version) | yes (loadIG) | loadIG |\n| bpWarnings | Ignore/Hint/Warning/Error | no | validate |\n| resourceIdRule | OPTIONAL/REQUIRED/PROHIBITED | no | validate |\n| includeContentInReport | boolean (default `true`) | no | validate |\n\n**Outputs:**\n| Name | Type |\n|------|------|\n| outcome | string (OperationOutcome JSON) |\n| severity | error/warning/information |\n| errors | string (count) |\n| warnings | string (count) |\n\nValidation issues → `result: SUCCESS` with counts. `FAILURE` only for infrastructure errors.",
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Service definition", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ServiceDefinition" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/fhir/process": {
      "post": {
        "tags": ["Validator"],
        "summary": "Validate a resource or load an IG",
        "operationId": "fhirProcess",
        "description": "**validate:** Validates `inputs.content` against `inputs.profiles`. The `inputs.contentType` selects the wire format (default `application/fhir+json`).\n\n**loadIG:** Loads `inputs.ig` (e.g. `hl7.fhir.be.medication#1.1.0`).",
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["operation", "inputs"],
                "properties": {
                  "operation": { "type": "string", "enum": ["validate", "loadIG"] },
                  "inputs": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                      "content": { "type": "string", "description": "FHIR resource as a string in the format named by `contentType` (for validate)" },
                      "contentType": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "MIME type of `content` (for validate). Optional; defaults to `application/fhir+json`.",
                        "enum": ["application/fhir+json", "application/fhir+xml", "text/turtle"],
                        "default": "application/fhir+json"
                      },
                      "profiles": { "type": "string", "description": "Comma-separated profile URLs (for validate)" },
                      "ig": { "type": "string", "description": "IG package e.g. hl7.fhir.be.core#2.1.2 (for loadIG)" },
                      "bpWarnings": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Ignore", "Hint", "Warning", "Error"] },
                      "resourceIdRule": { "type": "string", "enum": ["OPTIONAL", "REQUIRED", "PROHIBITED"] },
                      "includeContentInReport": {
                        "type": "boolean",
                        "description": "If true (default), the validated content is echoed back in the TAR report context so the ITB can show it inline alongside findings.",
                        "default": true
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "examples": {
                "validate": {
                  "summary": "Validate a Patient",
                  "value": { "operation": "validate", "inputs": { "content": "{\"resourceType\":\"Patient\",\"name\":[{\"family\":\"Smith\"}]}", "profiles": "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/Patient" } }
                },
                "validateXml": {
                  "summary": "Validate an XML resource",
                  "value": { "operation": "validate", "inputs": { "content": "<Patient xmlns=\"http://hl7.org/fhir\"><name><family value=\"Smith\"/></name></Patient>", "contentType": "application/fhir+xml" } }
                },
                "loadIG": {
                  "summary": "Load Belgian core IG",
                  "value": { "operation": "loadIG", "inputs": { "ig": "hl7.fhir.be.core#2.1.2" } }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Validation result. The body is a `ValidationResponse` carrying both a flat summary and a full TAR report with context items. `loadIG` returns a plain `ProcessResponse` shape (no TAR).",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ValidationResponse" },
                "examples": {
                  "validateClean": {
                    "summary": "Successful validation, content echoed in report context",
                    "value": {
                      "result": "SUCCESS",
                      "output": { "outcome": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[]}", "severity": "information", "errors": "0", "warnings": "0" },
                      "report": {
                        "id": "5b9b5e0c-2e2e-4c1b-9d6f-1f9c4f3a1abc",
                        "date": "2026-04-27T12:00:00Z",
                        "result": "SUCCESS",
                        "counters": { "nrOfErrors": 0, "nrOfWarnings": 0, "nrOfAssertions": 0 },
                        "overview": { "name": "HL7 FHIR Validator", "version": "6.9.8-SNAPSHOT" },
                        "items": [],
                        "context": [
                          {
                            "name": "operationOutcome",
                            "value": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[]}",
                            "embeddingMethod": "STRING",
                            "type": "string",
                            "mimeType": "application/fhir+json",
                            "forContext": true,
                            "forReport": true
                          },
                          {
                            "name": "content",
                            "value": "{\"resourceType\":\"Patient\",\"name\":[{\"family\":\"Smith\"}]}",
                            "embeddingMethod": "STRING",
                            "type": "string",
                            "mimeType": "application/fhir+json",
                            "forContext": true,
                            "forReport": true
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "validateWithError": {
                    "summary": "Validation finds a line-anchored error",
                    "value": {
                      "result": "FAILURE",
                      "output": { "outcome": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[{\"severity\":\"error\",\"code\":\"invalid\",\"details\":{\"text\":\"Patient.name.family is required\"}}]}", "severity": "error", "errors": "1", "warnings": "0" },
                      "report": {
                        "id": "8c1d2c4a-9d6f-4f1b-92e1-3c2a1f9b1def",
                        "date": "2026-04-27T12:00:00Z",
                        "result": "FAILURE",
                        "counters": { "nrOfErrors": 1, "nrOfWarnings": 0, "nrOfAssertions": 0 },
                        "overview": { "name": "HL7 FHIR Validator", "version": "6.9.8-SNAPSHOT" },
                        "items": [
                          { "level": "ERROR", "description": "Patient.name.family is required", "location": "content:3:5", "type": "invalid" }
                        ],
                        "context": [
                          {
                            "name": "operationOutcome",
                            "value": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[{\"severity\":\"error\",\"code\":\"invalid\",\"details\":{\"text\":\"Patient.name.family is required\"}}]}",
                            "embeddingMethod": "STRING",
                            "type": "string",
                            "mimeType": "application/fhir+json",
                            "forContext": true,
                            "forReport": true
                          },
                          {
                            "name": "content",
                            "value": "{\n  \"resourceType\": \"Patient\",\n  \"name\": [{}]\n}",
                            "embeddingMethod": "STRING",
                            "type": "string",
                            "mimeType": "application/fhir+json",
                            "forContext": true,
                            "forReport": true
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "loadIG": {
                    "summary": "loadIG (no TAR)",
                    "value": { "result": "SUCCESS", "output": { "loaded": "hl7.fhir.be.core#2.1.2" } }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/matchetype/definition": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Matchetype"],
        "summary": "MatchetypeProcessor — service definition",
        "operationId": "matchetypeDefinition",
        "description": "Returns GITB service metadata.\n\nService id: `MatchetypeProcessor`\nOperation: `compare`\n\n**Inputs:**\n| Name | Type | Required |\n|------|------|----------|\n| resource | string (FHIR JSON) | yes |\n| matchetype | string (FHIR JSON pattern) | yes |\n| mode | complete/partial | no (default: complete) |\n\n**Outputs:**\n| Name | Type |\n|------|------|\n| outcome | string (OperationOutcome JSON) |\n| severity | information (match) or error (mismatch) |",
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Service definition", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ServiceDefinition" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/matchetype/process": {
      "post": {
        "tags": ["Matchetype"],
        "summary": "Compare resource against a pattern",
        "operationId": "matchetypeProcess",
        "description": "Compares `inputs.resource` against `inputs.matchetype`. Both stringified FHIR JSON.",
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["operation", "inputs"],
                "properties": {
                  "operation": { "type": "string", "enum": ["compare"] },
                  "inputs": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": ["resource", "matchetype"],
                    "properties": {
                      "resource": { "type": "string", "description": "Actual FHIR resource as stringified JSON" },
                      "matchetype": { "type": "string", "description": "Expected pattern as stringified JSON" },
                      "mode": { "type": "string", "enum": ["complete", "partial"], "default": "complete" }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "example": {
                "operation": "compare",
                "inputs": {
                  "resource": "{\"resourceType\":\"Patient\",\"name\":[{\"family\":\"Smith\"}]}",
                  "matchetype": "{\"resourceType\":\"Patient\",\"name\":[{\"family\":\"Smith\"}]}"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Comparison result", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ProcessResponse" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/testdata/definition": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Test Data"],
        "summary": "TestDataGenerator — service definition",
        "operationId": "testdataDefinition",
        "description": "Returns GITB service metadata.\n\nService id: `TestDataGenerator`\nOperations: `generate`, `generateBundle`\n\n**Inputs:**\n| Name | Type | Required |\n|------|------|----------|\n| profile | string (canonical URL) | yes |\n| mappings | string (JSON array) | no |\n| data | string (JSON array) | no |\n\n**Outputs:**\n| Name | Type |\n|------|------|\n| resource | string (FHIR JSON) |",
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Service definition", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ServiceDefinition" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/testdata/process": {
      "post": {
        "tags": ["Test Data"],
        "summary": "Generate test data from a profile",
        "operationId": "testdataProcess",
        "description": "**generate:** Single resource from `inputs.profile`.\n**generateBundle:** Same, wrapped in a Bundle.",
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["operation", "inputs"],
                "properties": {
                  "operation": { "type": "string", "enum": ["generate", "generateBundle"] },
                  "inputs": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": ["profile"],
                    "properties": {
                      "profile": { "type": "string", "description": "Canonical URL of the StructureDefinition" },
                      "mappings": { "type": "string", "description": "Stringified JSON array of mapping objects" },
                      "data": { "type": "string", "description": "Stringified JSON array of data row objects" }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "example": { "operation": "generate", "inputs": { "profile": "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/Patient" } }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Generated resource", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ProcessResponse" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/validationResults/definition": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Validation Results"],
        "summary": "ValidationResultsProcessor — service definition",
        "operationId": "validationResultsDefinition",
        "description": "Returns GITB service metadata. Pure JSON utility — no FHIR engine needed.\n\nService id: `ValidationResultsProcessor`\nOperations: `summarize`, `filterBySeverity`, `filterByText`\n\n**Inputs:**\n| Name | Type | Required | Used by |\n|------|------|----------|---------|\n| outcome | string (OperationOutcome JSON) | yes | all |\n| severity | fatal/error/warning/information | yes | filterBySeverity |\n| text | string | yes | filterByText |\n\n**Outputs:**\n| Name | Type | Returned by |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| errors | string (count) | summarize |\n| warnings | string (count) | summarize |\n| count | string (count) | filterBySeverity, filterByText |",
        "responses": {
          "200": { "description": "Service definition", "content": { "application/json": { "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ServiceDefinition" } } } }
        }
      }
    },
    "/validationResults/process": {
      "post": {
        "tags": ["Validation Results"],
        "summary": "Summarize or filter validation results",
        "operationId": "validationResultsProcess",
        "description": "**summarize:** Counts errors/warnings in `inputs.outcome`.\n**filterBySeverity:** Counts issues matching `inputs.severity`.\n**filterByText:** Counts issues where details.text contains `inputs.text`.",
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["operation", "inputs"],
                "properties": {
                  "operation": { "type": "string", "enum": ["summarize", "filterBySeverity", "filterByText"] },
                  "inputs": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": ["outcome"],
                    "properties": {
                      "outcome": { "type": "string", "description": "OperationOutcome as stringified JSON" },
                      "severity": { "type": "string", "enum": ["fatal", "error", "warning", "information"], "description": "For filterBySeverity" },
                      "text": { "type": "string", "description": "For filterByText: substring to match" }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "examples": {
                "summarize": { "summary": "Count errors and warnings", "value": { "operation": "summarize", "inputs": { "outcome": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[{\"severity\":\"error\",\"code\":\"invalid\",\"details\":{\"text\":\"Bad\"}}]}" } } },
                "filterBySeverity": { "summary": "Count error-level issues", "value": { "operation": "filterBySeverity", "inputs": { "outcome": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[...]}", "severity": "error" } } },
                "filterByText": { "summary": "Count issues mentioning identifier", "value": { "operation": "filterByText", "inputs": { "outcome": "{\"resourceType\":\"OperationOutcome\",\"issue\":[...]}", "text": "identifier" } } }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Result",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ProcessResponse" },
                "example": { "result": "SUCCESS", "output": { "errors": "1", "warnings": "0" } }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "components": {
    "schemas": {
      "ServiceDefinition": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "GITB service definition",
        "properties": {
          "id": { "type": "string", "description": "Service identifier" },
          "operations": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } },
          "inputs": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "object", "properties": { "name": { "type": "string" }, "type": { "type": "string" }, "required": { "type": "boolean" } } } },
          "outputs": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "object", "properties": { "name": { "type": "string" }, "type": { "type": "string" } } } }
        }
      },
      "ProcessResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "GITB processing response",
        "properties": {
          "result": { "type": "string", "enum": ["SUCCESS", "FAILURE"], "description": "Whether the operation succeeded" },
          "output": { "type": "object", "additionalProperties": { "type": "string" }, "description": "Output parameters as string key-value pairs" },
          "error": { "type": "string", "description": "Error message (only when result is FAILURE)" }
        }
      },
      "EmbeddingMethod": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": ["STRING", "BASE_64", "URI"],
        "description": "How the value of an AnyContent item is encoded. STRING = raw text. BASE_64 = base64-encoded bytes. URI = a URL the server fetches (subject to SSRF allowlist)."
      },
      "AnyContent": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "GITB AnyContent wrapper for typed payloads carried in TAR context items. Used by the ITB to render values alongside report findings.",
        "required": ["name", "value", "embeddingMethod"],
        "properties": {
          "name": { "type": "string", "description": "Logical name of the item, e.g. `content`, `operationOutcome`, `fetchInfo`." },
          "value": { "type": "string", "description": "The payload, encoded according to `embeddingMethod`." },
          "embeddingMethod": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/EmbeddingMethod" },
          "type": { "type": "string", "description": "GITB simple type — typically `string`.", "default": "string" },
          "mimeType": { "type": "string", "description": "MIME type of `value`. Used by the test engine to pick a renderer (JSON viewer, XML viewer, …). Set by the service on outputs; ignored on inputs." },
          "encoding": { "type": "string", "description": "Character encoding of `value` (when textual).", "default": "UTF-8" },
          "forContext": { "type": "boolean", "description": "Include this item in the report's context (data the report refers to).", "default": true },
          "forReport": { "type": "boolean", "description": "Show this item in the report itself.", "default": true }
        }
      },
      "LevelType": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": ["ERROR", "WARNING", "INFO"],
        "description": "Severity level of a TAR report item."
      },
      "TestResultType": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": ["SUCCESS", "FAILURE", "WARNING", "UNDEFINED"],
        "description": "Aggregate validation result. `UNDEFINED` means the engine could not produce a definitive verdict (e.g. parse failure)."
      },
      "ValidationCounters": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "Aggregate issue counts.",
        "properties": {
          "nrOfErrors": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 0 },
          "nrOfWarnings": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 0 },
          "nrOfAssertions": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 0, "description": "Information-level findings." }
        }
      },
      "ValidationOverview": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "Summary metadata for the validation run.",
        "properties": {
          "name": { "type": "string", "description": "Human-readable validator name." },
          "version": { "type": "string", "description": "Validation engine version." },
          "note": { "type": "string", "description": "Free-form note. Echoes the test session id when supplied via `Gitb-Test-Session-Identifier`." },
          "profileID": { "type": "string", "description": "Profile (or main profile) the resource was validated against." }
        }
      },
      "ReportItem": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "A single finding in a TAR report.",
        "required": ["level", "description"],
        "properties": {
          "level": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/LevelType" },
          "description": { "type": "string", "description": "Human-readable issue text. Mapped from `OperationOutcome.issue.details.text`." },
          "location": { "type": "string", "description": "Where the issue applies. Either a JSON path (e.g. `Patient.name[0].family`) or, when line-anchored, `content:<line>:<col>` — referring to the AnyContent item named `content` in the report context. The latter form lets the ITB jump to the line in its inline editor." },
          "type": { "type": "string", "description": "Issue category, mapped from `OperationOutcome.issue.code`." },
          "value": { "type": "string", "description": "Engine diagnostics, when available." },
          "assertionID": { "type": "string", "description": "Rule/invariant identifier when the finding is tied to a named rule." }
        }
      },
      "TAR": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "GITB Test Assertion Report. Returned by validation services in place of a flat output map.",
        "properties": {
          "id": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid", "description": "Fresh UUID per call (distinct from `sessionId`)." },
          "date": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time", "description": "Server UTC timestamp." },
          "result": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/TestResultType" },
          "counters": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ValidationCounters" },
          "overview": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ValidationOverview" },
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ReportItem" },
            "description": "Per-issue findings."
          },
          "context": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/AnyContent" },
            "description": "Context items the report refers to. Always includes an `operationOutcome` AnyContent carrying the raw FHIR OperationOutcome JSON. When `inputs.includeContentInReport` is `true` (default), also includes a `content` AnyContent carrying the validated payload — this enables ITB inline rendering and line-anchored locations of the form `content:<line>:<col>`."
          }
        }
      },
      "ValidationResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "description": "Validation service response. `output` is the flat convenience summary (counts and severity) for callers that only need a quick read; `report` carries the full TAR with findings and context.",
        "properties": {
          "result": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/TestResultType" },
          "output": {
            "type": "object",
            "additionalProperties": { "type": "string" },
            "description": "Flat string map: `errors` (count), `warnings` (count), `severity` (highest seen), `outcome` (raw OperationOutcome JSON). Same data also present in `report.counters` and `report.context`."
          },
          "report": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/TAR" },
          "error": { "type": "string", "description": "Error message (only when `result` is `FAILURE` due to an infrastructure error, not a validation failure)." }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
